snippet.textDisplay:
Jimin said he’s not near anything like the dancers in the ”Black Swan” Art music video caus’ he is so humble! I’m a modern dancer and let me tell u that he is really on the same level as the dancers in this Art MV, and also has an unbelievable flexibility.

Jimin who has an amazing flexibility is unique and is brilliant in all dance genres from ballet to hiphop. He is also a contemporary/modern dancer since studying at Busan Highschool of Art and was a legendary top student. He even got to do a solo dance performance at one of his teachers’ weddings.

Trust me, he can without doubt do the same choreo in the Art MV to perfection if he only got the chance and enough time to rehearse! BTS has Jimin who is a modern/contemporary top dancer and I think they should have used Jimin in the music video to their song. Honestly, the MV would have gotten so much more attention from not only armys, but American artists, ppl in the showbiz as and general ppl as well.

Jimin deserves the spotlight at least one time, and to show his amazing skills to the International audience. Except armys, no people know about his incredible talent. I wish BigHit would let Jimin do a solo dance performance at an American TV show, or as an intro. His solo dance at ”Melon Music Awards” 2019 to an instrumental version of ”I need u” was breathtaking.
https://youtu.be/8D7Wnnow2kQ

https://youtu.be/3yttt76hXOs

21 year old Jimin opening ”SBS Gayo Daejun 2016” with modern/contemporary pro-dancers: https://youtu.be/oYpE5CdTiZE
https://youtu.be/vdOQsDO1gjA
As a dancer myself, I don’t think general people understand the strength and control Jimin has and never will. Look at his flawless lines, how he keeps his toes pointed in his jumps, the airtime and still manage to lands lightly which takes years of hard training to ever attain. He is on a whole other level even campared to these pro modern/contemporary dancers.

23 year old Jimin (along with J-hope and Jungkook who are the best dancers along with Jimin) performing at ”Melon music awards” 2018: https://youtu.be/XozYg4IuDgY

BTS is the best in the industry. Jimin really is on a whole other level than any idol we’ve seen though. He is humble, but yes he’s even better than regular pro dancers. I think it’s sad that he doesn’t get to show this to the world, only to the Korean audience at their award shows. He is quick, strong, incredibly flexible, sooo fluid, sooo smooth, shows the emotions of the song with his entire body and with such details in every move. He dances his heart out.
I also wish BTS would perform one of those epic powerful performances in America too (like ”We are Bulletproof pt.2” they did at MAMA 2019, or perform Dionysus). People would drop their jaws in awe and see them in a different way. Imagine the respect and love he/BTS would get. It would also shut down alot of antis who are down-grading their quality, talent, versatility and individual talent.

Moreover, I have seen alot of reaction videos were non Korean/American dancers, singers, choreographers and such have reacted to him/BTS. Many of them are surprised and say that they didn’t know he/BTS were this amazing. They are asking why he/they never get to do one of these epic performances for the American/International audience and say they would love to see this in the U.S.

after watching Black Swan, I wondered if bangtan would do a contemporary piece, or maybe something like Spring Day where it incorporated those elements
i do hope it's something like that; I bet Jimin would really love going back to his dance roots
His contemporary dances are done beautifully, and I'd be so happy to see him to get in touch with that side of himself again-- even Namjoon implies it'd be nice to see him that way 😊🌸

even so, I bet BTS' performance will still be amazing no matter what the final choreography is 💕 very excited for this album!!
